# Copy this file to .env.local (gitignored) at the parent workspace root and fill in your tokens.
# Restart your editor after editing.
#
# Stdio MCP servers: secrets load from this file automatically (via mcp-load-env on sync).
# HTTP Bearer MCP servers in Cursor: also add a one-time env load — see <workspace-repo>/setup.md §4.1.
#
# If you load this file into your shell (mcp:install-shell or source in ~/.zshrc), prefer a
# workspace-specific prefix on keys (e.g. ACME_SONAR_TOKEN) to avoid env collisions.
# Or launch the editor from a terminal after sourcing this file — see setup.md §4.1.
#
# Use the same variable names as placeholders in mcp.json (${VAR} for stdio, ${env:VAR} for HTTP headers), for example:
# ACME_MY_API_KEY=
